definition.value: An amino trisaccharide that is D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at posiitons 2 and 6 have been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl derivatives.
A D-glucofuranose that has alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.
A trisaccharide consisting of a beta-D-galactopyranose residue and two beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->2) and (1->6) glycosidic bonds.
